# filter out low abundance data
Aphyseq.tax.level <- phyloseq_filter_prevalence(Aphyseq.tax.level, prev.trh = 0.05, abund.trh = 100, threshold_condition = "AND", abund.type = "total")  

#prev.trh   = Prevalence threshold (default, 0.05 = 5% of samples)
#abund.trh = Abundance threshold (default, NULL). Abundance threshold defines if the OTU should be preserved if its abundance is larger than threshold (e.g., >= 50 reads)
#threshold_condition    = Indicates whether OTU should be kept if it occurs in many samples AND/OR it has high abundance - type of prevalence and abundance conditions, can be "OR" (default) or "AND"
#abund.type= Character string indicating which type of OTU abundance to take into account for filtering ("total", "mean", or "median")

otu_data <- as.matrix(Aphyseq.tax.level@otu_table@.Data)
otu_data <- t(otu_data)
otu_data <- as.data.frame(otu_data)

meta_data <- as.matrix(Aphyseq.tax.level@sam_data)
meta_data <- as.data.frame(meta_data)

top <- names(sort(taxa_sums(Aphyseq_norm_phylum), decreasing = TRUE))[1:N]
top2 <- names(sort(taxa_sums(Aphyseq_norm_phylum), decreasing = TRUE))[1:N2]
Aphyseq_norm_phylum_top <- prune_taxa(top2, Aphyseq_norm_phylum)

plot_abundance = function(Aphyseq_norm_phylum_top, ylabn = "",
                          Facet = "Phylum",
                          Color = "Phylum"){
  mAphyseq = psmelt(Aphyseq_norm_phylum_top)
  mAphyseq <- subset(mAphyseq, Abundance > 0)
  ggplot(data = mAphyseq,
         mapping = aes_string(x = "sample_type", y = "Abundance",
                              color = Color, fill = Color)) +
    geom_violin(fill = NA) +
    geom_point(size = 1, alpha = 0.3,
               position = position_jitter(width = 0.3)) +
    facet_wrap(facets = Facet) + ylab(ylabn) +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
    scale_y_log10()
}

AphyseqRA = transform_sample_counts(Aphyseq_norm_phylum_top, function(x){x / sum(x)})

#library("phyloseq")
#library("ggplot2")
#library("gridExtra")

plot_abundance(Aphyseq_norm_phylum_top,"Original Abundances")

plot_abundance(AphyseqRA, "Relative Abundances")
